e=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">http://www.example.com?controller=user&action=edit</span></tt>”. Pretty <em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">URL</em>‘s may be used to shorten <em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">URL</em>‘s for textual representation or search engine optimization (<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">SEO</em>), but they do not directly affect the functionality of the application.</div><div class=\"section\" id=\"php-version\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(15, 20, 25); font-family: Lato, sans-serif;\"><span id=\"requirements-version\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></span><h3 style=\"margin: 20px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.1; color: black; font-size: 24px;\">PHP Version<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"https://framework.zend.com/manual/2.0/en/ref/requirements.html#php-version\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 4px; color: rgb(36, 185, 255); transition: background-color 0.4s linear 0s, color 0.4s linear 0s; font-size: 0.6em; font-weight: normal;\">¶</a></h3><div>Zend recommends the most current release of <em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">PHP</em> for critical security and performance enhancements, and currently supports <em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">PHP</em> 5.2.4 or later.</div><div>Zend Framework has an extensive collection of unit tests, which you can run using PHPUnit 3.3.0 or later.</div></div><div class=\"section\" id=\"php-extensions\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(15, 20, 25); font-family: Lato, sans-serif;\"><span id=\"requirements-extensions\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></span><h3 style=\"margin: 20px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.1; color: black; font-size: 24px;\">PHP Extensions<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"https://framework.zend.com/manual/2.0/en/ref/requirements.html#php-extensions\" title=\"Permalink 