; in most cases the framework can be used without them, although performance may suffer or ancillary features may not be fully functional. An example of such a dependency is mod_rewrite in an Apache environment, which can be used to implement “pretty <em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">URL</em>‘s” like “<tt class=\"docutils literal\" style=\"margin: 0px 2px; padding: 0px 5px; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248); border: 1px solid rgb(234, 234, 234); border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.9em;\"><span class=\"pre\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">http://www.example.com/user/edit</span></tt>”. If mod_rewrite is not enabled, Zend Framework can be configured to support <em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">URL</em>‘s such as “<tt class=\"docutils literal\" style=\"margin: 0px 2px; padding: 0px 5px; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248); border: 1px solid rgb(234, 234, 234); border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.9em;\"><span class=\"pre\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">http://www.example.com?controller=user&action=edit</span></tt>”. Pretty <em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">URL</em>‘s may be used to shorten <em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">URL</em>‘s for textual representation or search engine optimization (<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">SEO</em>), but they do not directly affect the functionality of the application.</div><div class=\"section\" id=\"php-version\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(15, 20, 25); font-family: Lato, sans-serif;\"><span id=\"requirements-version\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></span><h3 style=\"margin: 20px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.1; color: black; font-size: 24px;\">PHP Version<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"https://framework.zend.com/manual/2.0/en/ref/requirements.html#php-version\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 4px; color: rgb(36, 185, 255); transition: background-color 0.4s linear 0s,